    "documentation": "# AI Agent for Conversational Document Q&A\n\n## Project Description\nThe AI Agent for Conversational Document Q&A is a Streamlit-based application designed to facilitate interactive questioning and answering over user-uploaded PDF documents. It leverages advanced natural language processing capabilities through Langchain and OpenAI's large language models (LLMs) to provide an intelligent conversational interface. The system implements Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) by converting document content into embeddings stored in ChromaDB, enabling the AI to retrieve relevant information contextually for generating accurate and coherent responses.\n\n## Features\n*   **PDF Document Upload:** Users can easily upload PDF files directly through the web interface.\n*   **Conversational Q&A:** Engage in natural language conversations with the AI to ask questions about the uploaded document's content.\n*   **Intelligent Context Retrieval:** Utilizes Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to fetch relevant document chunks based on user queries, ensuring answers are grounded in the provided text.\n*   **Persistent Chat History:** Maintains the conversation context throughout the session, allowing for follow-up questions and more natural interactions.\n*   **OpenAI LLM Integration:** Powered by OpenAI's sophisticated language models for understanding questions and generating comprehensive answers.\n*   **Streamlit User Interface:** Provides an intuitive and interactive web application experience.\n\n## Dependencies\nThe project requires the following Python libraries:\n*   `langchain`: Framework for developing applications powered by language models.\n*   `openai`: Python client library for the OpenAI API.\n*   `python-dotenv`: For loading environment variables from a `.env` file.\n*   `streamlit`: For building interactive web applications.\n*   `tiktoken`: Byte-pair encoding tokenizer for OpenAI models.\n*   `chromadb`: Open-source vector database for storing and querying embeddings.\n*   `pypdf`: A pure-Python PDF library for reading PDF files.\n*   `pandas`: Data analysis and manipulation tool (listed in requirements, potential for future data processing).\n*   `matplotlib`: Plotting library (listed in requirements, potential for future data visualization).\n*   `scikit-learn`: Machine learning library (listed in requirements, potential for future ML tasks).\n*   `plotly`: Interactive graphing library (listed in requirements, potential for future interactive plots).\n\n## Usage Instructions\n\nTo set up and run the AI Agent locally, follow these steps:\n\n1.  **Clone the Repository:**\n    ```bash\n    git clone https://github.com/PrajwaL-N-TECHIE/AI_Agent-.git\n    cd AI_Agent-\n    ```\n\n2.  **Create a Virtual Environment (Recommended):**\n    ```bash\n    python -m venv venv\n    source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\\Scripts\\activate`\n    ```\n\n3.  **Install Dependencies:**\n    ```bash\n    pip install -r requirements.txt\n    ```\n\n4.  **Set Up OpenAI API Key:**\n    *   Obtain an API key from your OpenAI account.\n    *   Create a file named `.env` in the root directory of the project.\n    *   Add your OpenAI API key to the `.env` file in the following format:\n        ```\n        OPENAI_API_KEY=\"your_openai_api_key_here\"\n        ```\n\n5.  **Run the Application:**\n    ```bash\n    streamlit run app.py\n    ```\n\n6.  **Access the Application:**\n    Open your web browser and navigate to the URL displayed in your terminal (usually `http://localhost:8501`). You can then upload a PDF file and start conversing with the AI agent.\n\n## API Documentation (if applicable)\nThis project is a Streamlit-based web application and does not expose a direct RESTful API for external consumption. All interactions occur through the web user interface.\n\n## Code Explanation\n\n### `app.py`\nThis is the main application file that orchestrates the Streamlit UI, document processing, and conversational logic.\n\n*   **Environment Setup:** Loads the `OPENAI_API_KEY` from the `.env` file.\n*   **LLM Initialization:** Initializes `ChatOpenAI` as the primary language model for generating responses and `OpenAIEmbeddings` for converting text into vector representations.\n*   **Document Processing (`get_retriever` function):**\n    *   Takes a PDF file path as input.\n    *   Uses `PyPDFLoader` to load the document.\n    *   Employs `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` to break the document into manageable chunks.\n    *   Creates a `Chroma` vector store from these chunks and their embeddings.\n    *   Returns a `retriever` instance, which is capable of fetching relevant document chunks given a query.\n*   **Conversational Chain Setup (`get_conversational_chain` function):**\n    *   Initializes `ConversationalRetrievalChain` from Langchain. This chain is designed for Q&A over documents with memory.\n    *   It uses `ChatOpenAI` as the LLM, the configured retriever, and includes `ConversationBufferMemory` to maintain chat history.\n    *   Custom prompts from `prompts.py` are integrated to guide the LLM's behavior.\n*   **Streamlit UI (`main` function):**\n    *   Sets the application title.\n    *   Provides a file uploader for PDF files.\n    *   Upon PDF upload:\n        *   Processes the PDF to create a retriever.\n        *   Initializes the conversational chain.\n        *   Manages `st.session_state` to store and display chat history.\n        *   Displays previous messages.\n        *   Accepts user input in a chat box.\n        *   On user input, queries the conversational chain and displays the AI's response.\n\n### `prompts.py`\nThis file contains the custom prompt templates used by the Langchain conversational chain.\n\n*   **`SYSTEM_TEMPLATE`:** A high-level instruction provided to the LLM that sets the context for the conversation. It guides the AI to act as a helpful assistant that answers questions based *only* on the provided context, emphasizing not to fabricate information.\n*   **`CONDENSE_QUESTION_PROMPT`:** Used by the `ConversationalRetrievalChain` to condense new follow-up questions into a standalone question, taking into account the chat history. This ensures the AI can understand the current question without always needing to refer to previous turns explicitly.\n\n## Architecture Overview\nThe AI Agent's architecture follows a typical Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pattern, integrated within a Streamlit web application.\n\n1.  **User Interface (Streamlit):** The user interacts with the system through a web-based interface built with Streamlit. This interface handles PDF uploads and displays the chat conversation.\n2.  **Document Ingestion:**\n    *   When a user uploads a PDF, `PyPDFLoader` reads the document content.\n    *   `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` then breaks the text into smaller, manageable chunks suitable for embedding.\n3.  **Vector Store Creation:**\n    *   `OpenAIEmbeddings` convert these text chunks into numerical vector embeddings.\n    *   These embeddings are stored in `ChromaDB`, which acts as a vector database, allowing for efficient semantic search.\n4.  **Conversational AI Core (Langchain):**\n    *   `ConversationalRetrievalChain` from Langchain orchestrates the Q&A process.\n    *   It maintains `ConversationBufferMemory` to keep track of the chat history.\n5.  **Query Processing and Retrieval:**\n    *   When a user asks a question, the `ConversationalRetrievalChain` first uses the `CONDENSE_QUESTION_PROMPT` to refine the current query based on chat history.\n    *   This refined query is then embedded.\n    *   The embedded query is used to perform a similarity search in `ChromaDB`, retrieving the most relevant document chunks (context).\n6.  **Response Generation (OpenAI LLM):**\n    *   The retrieved document chunks, the condensed user question, and the `SYSTEM_TEMPLATE` are combined and passed to `ChatOpenAI` (the LLM).\n    *   The LLM generates a coherent and contextually relevant answer.\n7.  **Display:** The AI's response is then displayed back to the user in the Streamlit chat interface.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[User] -->|Upload PDF| B(Streamlit UI - app.py)\n    B -->|PDF File| C[PyPDFLoader]\n    C --> D[RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter]\n    D --> E[OpenAIEmbeddings]\n    E --> F[ChromaDB - Vector Store]\n\n    A -->|Ask Question| B\n    B -->|User Query| G[ConversationalRetrievalChain (Langchain)]\n    G -->|Refine Question (prompts.py)| H[Query Embedding]\n    H -->|Search Relevant Chunks| F\n    F -->|Relevant Chunks| G\n    B -->|Chat History| G\n    G -->|Context + Refined Query| I[ChatOpenAI - LLM]\n    I -->|AI Response| B\n    B -->|Display Response| A\n\n    subgraph Langchain Components\n        G\n    end\n    subgraph OpenAI Services\n        E\n        I\n    end\n    subgraph Data Stores\n        F\n    end\n```"
  },
