    "documentation": "# AI Agent\n## Project Description\nThe `AI Agent` project appears to be a full-stack application designed to interact with and manage various AI-driven functionalities, possibly related to drone operations, terrain analysis, and recommendation systems. It consists of a Python-based backend API and a React.js-based frontend user interface. The project utilizes MongoDB for data storage and is structured to allow for scalable development and easy deployment.\n\nThe frontend includes dedicated pages for a dashboard, drone panel, terrain visualization, and recommendations, suggesting a comprehensive system for monitoring, controlling, and analyzing data, likely from drones or similar autonomous agents, enhanced with AI capabilities.\n\n## Features\n*   **Interactive Dashboard:** A central hub for monitoring system status and key metrics.\n*   **Drone Panel:** Interface for managing and potentially controlling drone operations (e.g., flight paths, mission parameters).\n*   **Terrain Visualization:** Capabilities to display and analyze geographical or environmental data, possibly collected by drones.\n*   **Recommendations Engine:** An AI-powered system providing suggestions or insights, likely based on processed data (e.g., optimal drone routes, target areas for data collection, object identification).\n*   **RESTful API:** A Python backend exposing endpoints for data management and interaction with AI models or services.\n*   **Modern User Interface:** A responsive and component-based frontend built with React.js and a UI library (likely Shadcn UI).\n*   **Configuration Flexibility:** Environment variables for easy configuration of database connections and other settings.\n*   **Extensible Plugin System (Frontend):** Support for frontend plugins (e.g., `health-check`, `visual-edits`) to add new functionalities.\n*   **Testing Infrastructure:** Dedicated directories for backend and frontend tests to ensure code quality and reliability.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Backend\n*   **Python 3.x:** The core language for the backend server.\n*   **MongoDB:** A NoSQL database used for data persistence. The connection URL and database name are configured via environment variables.\n*   **Python Libraries:** (Inferred from `requirements.txt`)\n    *   Likely web framework (e.g., Flask, FastAPI, Django REST Framework).\n    *   MongoDB driver (e.g., `pymongo`).\n    *   Libraries for AI/ML tasks (e.g., `scikit-learn`, `tensorflow`, `pytorch`, `numpy`, `pandas`) based on the \"AI Agent\" title and \"Recommendations\" feature.\n    *   Environment variable management (`python-dotenv`).\n\n### Frontend\n*   **Node.js & npm/yarn:** JavaScript runtime and package manager.\n*   **React.js:** A JavaScript library for building user interfaces.\n*   **Craco:** (Create React App Configuration Override) A tool used to customize Create React App configurations without ejecting.\n*   **PostCSS & Tailwind CSS:** CSS tooling for efficient and utility-first styling.\n*   **Babel:** JavaScript compiler, specifically for transforming modern JavaScript and JSX.\n*   **Frontend UI Components:** (Inferred from `components/ui` directory names)\n    *   `accordion`, `alert-dialog`, `alert`, `aspect-ratio`, `avatar`, `badge`, `breadcrumb`, `button`, `calendar`, `card`, `carousel`, `checkbox`, `collapsible`, `command`, `context-menu`, `dialog`, `drawer`, `dropdown-menu`, `form`, `hover-card`, `input-otp`, `input`, `label`, `menubar`, `navigation-menu`, `pagination`, `popover`, `progress`, `radio-group`, `resizable`, `scroll-area`, `select`, `separator`, `sheet`, `skeleton`, `slider`, `sonner`, `switch`, `table`, `tabs`, `textarea`, `toast`, `toaster`, `toggle-group`, `toggle`, `tooltip`.\n    *   These suggest a UI library like [Shadcn UI](https://ui.shadcn.com/) or similar, built on Radix UI primitives and Tailwind CSS.\n*   **Frontend Utilities/Hooks:**\n    *   `use-toast.js`: Custom hook for managing toast notifications.\n    *   `utils.js`: General utility functions.\n\n## Usage Instructions\n\nTo set up and run the AI Agent application, follow these steps:\n\n### Prerequisites\n*   Git\n*   Python 3.8+\n*   Node.js 18+ & npm (or yarn)\n*   MongoDB instance (local or remote)\n\n### 1. Clone the Repository\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/your-repo/AI_Agent.git # Replace with actual repository URL\ncd AI_Agent--main\n```\n\n### 2. Backend Setup\n1.  Navigate to the `backend` directory:\n    ```bash\n    cd backend\n    ```\n2.  Create a Python virtual environment and activate it:\n    ```bash\n    python -m venv venv\n    # On Windows\n    .\\venv\\Scripts\\activate\n    # On macOS/Linux\n    source venv/bin/activate\n    ```\n3.  Install the required Python packages:\n    ```bash\n    pip install -r requirements.txt # Assuming requirements.txt exists and lists all dependencies\n    ```\n4.  Create a `.env` file in the `backend` directory and configure your MongoDB connection:\n    ```\n    MONGO_URL=\"mongodb://localhost:27017\" # Or your MongoDB connection string\n    DB_NAME=\"ai_agent_db\" # Or your preferred database name\n    CORS_ORIGINS=\"*\" # Adjust for production environments (e.g., \"http://localhost:3000\")\n    ```\n5.  Run the backend server:\n    ```bash\n    python server.py\n    ```\n    The backend API should now be running, typically on `http://localhost:5000` (or as configured in `server.py`).\n\n### 3. Frontend Setup\n1.  Navigate to the `frontend` directory:\n    ```bash\n    cd ../frontend\n    ```\n2.  Install the Node.js dependencies using `yarn` (as indicated by `yarn.lock`):\n    ```bash\n    yarn install\n    ```\n3.  Create a `.env` file in the `frontend` directory:\n    ```\n    # Example:\n    REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=\"http://localhost:5000\" # Or your backend API URL\n    ```\n4.  Start the frontend development server:\n    ```bash\n    yarn start\n    ```\n    The frontend application should open in your browser, typically at `http://localhost:3000`.\n\n### 4. Running Tests\n*   **Backend Tests:**\n    ```bash\n    cd backend\n    python -m unittest backend_test.py # Or pytest if configured\n    ```\n*   **Frontend Tests:**\n    ```bash\n    cd frontend\n    yarn test\n    ```\n\n## API Documentation (Inferred)\nThe backend (`server.py`) is expected to expose a RESTful API for interaction with the frontend and potentially external services. Given the project structure, the following general endpoints are anticipated:\n\n**Base URL:** `http://localhost:5000` (or as configured in your `.env`)\n\n### Health Check\n-   **Endpoint:** `/api/health`\n-   **Method:** `GET`\n-   **Description:** Checks the health and status of the backend API.\n-   **Request & Response Example:**\n    *   **Request:**\n        ```\n        GET /api/health\n        ```\n    *   **Response (200 OK):**\n        ```json\n        {\n            \"status\": \"healthy\",\n            \"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T10:00:00Z\"\n        }\n        ```\n\n### Drone Management\n-   **Endpoint:** `/api/drones`\n-   **Method:** `GET`\n-   **Description:** Retrieves a list of all registered drones.\n-   **Request & Response Example:**\n    *   **Request:**\n        ```\n        GET /api/drones\n        ```\n    *   **Response (200 OK):**\n        ```json\n        [\n            {\"id\": \"DRN001\", \"name\": \"Explorer 1\", \"status\": \"active\", \"battery\": 85},\n            {\"id\": \"DRN002\", \"name\": \"Surveyor X\", \"status\": \"idle\", \"battery\": 60}\n        ]\n        ```\n-   **Endpoint:** `/api/drones/{drone_id}`\n-   **Method:** `GET`\n-   **Description:** Retrieves details for a specific drone.\n-   **Request & Response Example:**\n    *   **Request:**\n        ```\n        GET /api/drones/DRN001\n        ```\n    *   **Response (200 OK):**\n        ```json\n        {\"id\": \"DRN001\", \"name\": \"Explorer 1\", \"status\": \"active\", \"battery\": 85, \"location\": {\"lat\": 34.0522, \"lon\": -118.2437}}\n        ```\n-   **Endpoint:** `/api/drones/{drone_id}/command`\n-   **Method:** `POST`\n-   **Description:** Sends a command to a specific drone (e.g., \"takeoff\", \"land\", \"fly_to\").\n-   **Request & Response Example:**\n    *   **Request:**\n        ```\n        POST /api/drones/DRN001/command\n        Content-Type: application/json\n\n        {\n            \"command\": \"fly_to\",\n            \"parameters\": {\"latitude\": 34.0, \"longitude\": -118.0, \"altitude\": 100}\n        }\n        ```\n    *   **Response (200 OK):**\n        ```json\n        {\"status\": \"command_sent\", \"drone_id\": \"DRN001\", \"command\": \"fly_to\"}\n        ```\n\n### Terrain Data\n-   **Endpoint:** `/api/terrain`\n-   **Method:** `GET`\n-   **Description:** Retrieves available terrain data or metadata for visualization.\n-   **Request & Response Example:**\n    *   **Request:**\n        ```\n        GET /api/terrain?area=region_a\n        ```\n    *   **Response (200 OK):**\n        ```json\n        {\"area\": \"region_a\", \"data_url\": \"/assets/terrain/region_a.geojson\", \"resolution\": \"high\"}\n        ```\n\n### Recommendations\n-   **Endpoint:** `/api/recommendations`\n-   **Method:** `GET`\n-   **Description:** Fetches AI-generated recommendations (e.g., optimal flight paths, points of interest).\n-   **Request & Response Example:**\n    *   **Request:**\n        ```\n        GET /api/recommendations?type=flight_path&drone_id=DRN001\n        ```\n    *   **Response (200 OK):**\n        ```json\n        {\n            \"type\": \"flight_path\",\n            \"recommendation\": [\n                {\"lat\": 34.0, \"lon\": -118.0},\n                {\"lat\": 34.1, \"lon\": -118.1},\n                {\"lat\": 34.2, \"lon\": -118.2}\n            ],\n            \"confidence\": 0.95\n        }\n        ```\n\n### Design Guidelines\n-   **Endpoint:** `/api/design_guidelines`\n-   **Method:** `GET`\n-   **Description:** Retrieves the project's design guidelines.\n-   **Request & Response Example:**\n    *   **Request:**\n        ```\n        GET /api/design_guidelines\n        ```\n    *   **Response (200 OK):**\n        ```json\n        {\n            \"colors\": {\"primary\": \"#3B82F6\", \"secondary\": \"#6B7280\"},\n            \"typography\": {\"font_family\": \"Inter\", \"base_size\": 16},\n            \"components\": [\"buttons\", \"cards\", \"forms\"]\n        }\n        ```\n\n## Code Explanation\n\n### Backend\n*   **`backend/server.py`**: This is the main entry point for the backend application. It likely sets up a web server (e.g., using Flask or FastAPI), defines API routes, handles incoming HTTP requests, interacts with the MongoDB database, and potentially orchestrates calls to AI models or external services.\n*   **`backend/requirements.txt`**: Lists all Python dependencies required for the backend. These are installed using `pip`.\n*   **`backend/.env`**: Contains environment-specific configurations like database connection strings (`MONGO_URL`), database names (`DB_NAME`), and Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) settings (`CORS_ORIGINS`).\n\n### Frontend\n*   **`frontend/src/App.js`**: The root component of the React application. It typically defines the main layout, routing logic, and orchestrates other components.\n*   **`frontend/src/index.js`**: The entry point for the React application, responsible for rendering the `App` component into the DOM.\n*   **`frontend/src/App.css` / `frontend/src/index.css`**: Global CSS files for the application, likely containing base styles and utility classes.\n*   **`frontend/tailwind.config.js` / `frontend/postcss.config.js`**: Configuration files for Tailwind CSS and PostCSS, which process CSS to provide utilities and optimize styling.\n*   **`frontend/craco.config.js`**: Configuration file for Craco, allowing custom webpack configurations without ejecting the Create React App setup. This is often used for things like path aliases or custom plugins.\n*   **`frontend/src/pages/`**: This directory contains the main views or screens of the application:\n    *   **`Dashboard.js`**: Displays an overview of the system, potentially with summaries of drone status, mission progress, and key AI insights.\n    *   **`DronePanel.js`**: Provides controls and real-time data for managing individual or groups of drones.\n    *   **`Recommendations.js`**: Presents AI-generated recommendations to the user, perhaps for mission planning or data analysis.\n    *   **`TerrainView.js`**: Visualizes geographical data, possibly with overlays of drone paths, points of interest, or AI analysis results.\n*   **`frontend/src/components/`**: Contains reusable UI components, often broken down into general-purpose UI elements (`ui/`) and application-specific components (e.g., `Navigation.js`).\n    *   **`Navigation.js`**: Likely handles the application's navigation menu or header.\n    *   **`ui/` (e.g., `button.jsx`, `dialog.jsx`, `table.jsx`)**: A collection of atomic UI components (likely from a headless UI library like Shadcn UI) that ensure a consistent look and feel across the application.\n*   **`frontend/src/hooks/use-toast.js`**: A custom React hook for managing and displaying toast notifications (small, temporary messages) throughout the application.\n*   **`frontend/src/lib/utils.js`**: Contains general utility functions that can be used across various parts of the frontend application.\n*   **`design_guidelines.json`**: A JSON file outlining design tokens and guidelines for the UI, ensuring consistency in styling and component usage.\n\n## Architecture Overview\nThe `AI Agent` project follows a typical client-server (or microservices-oriented) architecture:\n\n1.  **Frontend (Client-side):** A single-page application (SPA) built with React.js. It provides the user interface, handles user interactions, and visualizes data. It communicates with the backend API to fetch and send data.\n2.  **Backend (Server-side):** A Python application (e.g., Flask, FastAPI) responsible for business logic, data processing, and exposing a RESTful API. It acts as an intermediary between the frontend and the database, and potentially external AI/ML services or drone control systems.\n3.  **Database:** MongoDB, a NoSQL database, used for storing application data, user information, drone states, terrain data, and recommendation results.\n\nThe frontend is modular, separating concerns into pages and reusable UI components. It leverages modern JavaScript tooling (Craco, Tailwind CSS) for efficient development. The backend handles data persistence and serves as the computational hub, integrating AI capabilities.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    User[End User] -->|Interacts with| Frontend(React.js Application)\n    Frontend -->|HTTP/REST API Calls| Backend(Python Server - e.g., Flask/FastAPI)\n    Backend -->|Data Persistence (CRUD)| Database[MongoDB]\n    Backend -->|AI/ML Operations| AIServices(AI/ML Models & Algorithms)\n    Backend -->|Drone Commands & Data| DroneControlSystem[External Drone Control System]\n\n    subgraph Frontend Components\n        DashboardPage[Dashboard.js]\n        DronePanelPage[DronePanel.js]\n        TerrainViewPage[TerrainView.js]\n        RecommendationsPage[Recommendations.js]\n        Navigation[Navigation.js]\n        UIComponents[UI Components (Buttons, Forms, etc.)]\n        CustomHooks[Custom Hooks (e.g., use-toast)]\n    end\n\n    Frontend --> DashboardPage\n    Frontend --> DronePanelPage\n    Frontend --> TerrainViewPage\n    Frontend --> RecommendationsPage\n    Frontend --> Navigation\n    Frontend --> UIComponents\n    Frontend --> CustomHooks\n\n    style User fill:#ace,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style Frontend fill:#bbf,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style Backend fill:#cfc,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style Database fill:#fcf,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style AIServices fill:#ddf,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style DroneControlSystem fill:#ffd,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n```"
